EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to public employees; making appropriations and
authorizations for the payment of quarterly retention
incentives, the implementation of certain provisions of
certain collective bargaining agreements and the payment
of salary increases for certain public employees; providing
that certain provisions of collective bargaining agreements
to which the State is a party are void; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
1 WHEREAS, The implementation of collective bargaining for
2 certain state employees provides an efficient mechanism for those
3 employees to have a voice in the terms and conditions of their
4 employment; and
5 WHEREAS, The Legislature, although recognizing the
6 tremendous service of those state employees, has a responsibility to
7 ensure the financial solvency of this State; and
8 WHEREAS, Economic conditions in this State can change rapidly
9 based on many factors often outside the control of the Legislature
10 and, as a result, funding all the provisions negotiated in such
11 collective bargaining agreements may be limited by these economic
12 realities; now therefore,
